Only two colors were visible on the surface of Mercury: black and gold. The black was the planet\u8217?s land, and its low reflectance meant that even under close illumination from the fierce sun, it remained a sheet of black. The gold was the sun, which occupied a considerable portion of the sky. In its broad wheel you could clearly see the surging of its fiery seas and the sunspots drifting by like black clouds, and, at its edges, the graceful dance of solar prominences.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
