As the meeting commenced, the United States, United Kingdom, France, and Germany put up another proposition, this one demanding the immediate suspension of Rey Diaz\u8217?s position as Wallfacer and his trial before the International Court of Justice for crimes against humanity.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
The US representative declared, \u8220?After substantial investigation, we believe that Rey Diaz\u8217?s strategic intent as disclosed by the Wallbreaker is credible. What we are facing now is a person whose crime dwarfs all of the crimes ever committed in human history. We were unable to find a single law applicable to his crime, so we recommend that the crime of Extinction of Life on Earth be added to international law, and that Rey Diaz be tried under it.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
Rey Diaz appeared quite relaxed at the hearing. Sneering, he said to the US representative, \u8220?You\u8217?ve been trying to get rid of me, haven\u8217?t you? Ever since the Wallfacer Project began, you have all applied a double standard to the Wallfacers. I\u8217?m the one you like least.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
The UK representative retorted, \u8220?Wallfacer Rey Diaz\u8217?s claim is baseless. In fact, the countries he is accusing are the ones who invested the most money into his plan, far exceeding what they invested in the other three Wallfacers.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Sure,\u8221? Rey Diaz said with a nod, \u8220?but the real reason you invested so heavily in my plan is because you wanted to get your hands on the stellar hydrogen bombs.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Ridiculous! What would we do with them?\u8221? the US representative shot back. \u8220?They\u8217?re incredibly inefficient weapons in a space battle, and on the Earth, there\u8217?s no practical significance even for those old twenty-megaton hydrogen bombs, much less a three-hundred-megaton monster.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
Rey Diaz responded calmly, \u8220?But the bombs will be the most effective weapon in battles on other planets, particularly in wars among humans. On the desolate surface of other planets, there\u8217?s no need to be concerned with civilian casualties or environmental damage, so you\u8217?re free to carry out wide-area destruction, or even a devastating sweep of the entire surface. Here\u8217?s where the stellar hydrogen bombs will prove useful. You must have anticipated that, as humanity expands into the Solar System, Earth\u8217?s conflicts will expand outward as well. This won\u8217?t change even with Trisolaris as a common enemy, and you\u8217?re preparing for it. Right now, it\u8217?s politically indefensible to develop superweapons for use against humans, so you took advantage of me to make them.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
The US representative said, \u8220?That\u8217?s the preposterous logic of a terrorist and a dictator. Rey Diaz is the kind of man who, granted the status and power of a Wallfacer, turns the Wallfacer Project into as big a danger as the Trisolaran invasion. We must take decisive action to correct this mistake.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?They\u8217?re as good as their word,\u8221? Rey Diaz said, turning to Garanin, the incumbent rotating chair. \u8220?The CIA has men waiting outside to arrest me as soon as I go outside after this hearing.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
The rotating chair glanced in the direction of the US representative, who was fiddling intently with his pen. Garanin had first taken office at the start of the Wallfacer Project, and even he had forgotten the number of short terms in office he had served during the ensuing two decades. But this was the last time. Now white-haired, he was about to retire.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Wallfacer Rey Diaz, if what you say is true, then that is inappropriate. So long as the principles of the Wallfacer Project still hold, Wallfacers have legal immunity, and none of their words and actions can be used as evidence to charge them of a crime,\u8221? he said.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Additionally, please remember that this is international territory,\u8221? the Japanese representative said.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?So does that mean,\u8221? the US representative said, raising a pencil, \u8220?that even when Rey Diaz is about to detonate the million superbombs he\u8217?s buried on Mercury, society still won\u8217?t be able to charge him with a crime?\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?According to the relevant provisions in the Wallfacer Act, placing limitations and curbs on the strategic plans of Wallfacers who exhibit dangerous tendencies is an entirely separate matter from the Wallfacer\u8217?s own legal immunity,\u8221? Garanin said.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Rey Diaz\u8217?s crimes have crossed outside the boundary of legal immunity. He must be punished. This is a precondition for the continued existence of the Wallfacer Project,\u8221? the UK representative said.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?May I remind the chair and the representatives,\u8221? Rey Diaz said, rising from his seat, \u8220?that this is a PDC Wallfacer hearing, and that I\u8217?m not on trial.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?You\u8217?ll stand in court soon,\u8221? the US representative said, with a chilly smile.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?I agree with Wallfacer Rey Diaz. We should return to the discussion of his strategic plan,\u8221? Garanin said, seizing the opportunity to temporarily bypass the thorny issue.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
The Japanese representative broke his silence. \u8220?From the way it looks now, the representatives have reached a consensus on the following point: Rey Diaz\u8217?s strategic plan exhibits dangerous tendencies toward clear violations of human rights, and according to the relevant principles in the Wallfacer Act, it should be stopped.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Then Proposition P269, proposed at the previous Wallfacer hearing, regarding halting Rey Diaz\u8217?s strategic plan, can now be put to a vote,\u8221? Garanin said.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Mr. Chair, wait one moment.\u8221? Rey Diaz raised his hand. \u8220?Before the vote, I hope I might be able to offer a final explanation of some of the details of my plan.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?If they\u8217?re just details, is this really necessary?\u8221? someone asked.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Save it for court,\u8221? the UK representative said sarcastically.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?No, these details are important,\u8221? Rey Diaz persisted. \u8220?Right now, let us assume that what the Wallbreaker has disclosed about my strategic intentions is true. One representative spoke of the moment when the million hydrogen bombs deployed on Mercury are ready to be detonated, at which point I will face the omnipresent sophons and declare to Trisolaris humanity\u8217?s intent to die with them. What will happen then?\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?The Trisolarans\u8217? reaction can\u8217?t be predicted, but on Earth, it\u8217?s certain that billions of people will want to wring your neck, just like you did to that Wallbreaker,\u8221? the French representative said.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
\u8220?Exactly. So I took certain measures to deal with such a situation. Take a look at this.\u8221? Rey Diaz raised his left hand and displayed his wristwatch to the assembly. It was entirely black, and the dial was twice as large and thick as a normal men\u8217?s watch, although it didn\u8217?t appear large on his thick wrist. \u8220?This is a transmitter sending a signal through a space link directly to Mercury.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
