\u8220?That\u8217?s only an expression, of course. Just a nonrigorous\~\u8230? analogy.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}I know that at least Trisolaris has love. But because it was not conducive to the civilization\u8217?s overall survival, it was suppressed when it had only just germinated. Yet the seed possesses a stubborn vitality, and will still grow in certain individuals.{	
\u8220?May I ask who you are?\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}We\u8217?ve never met. I was the operator who transmitted the warning to Earth two and a half centuries ago.{	
\u8220?My god, and you\u8217?re still alive?\u8221? Zhuang Yan exclaimed.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}I won\u8217?t be for much longer. I\u8217?ve been in a dehydrated state, but over the long years, even a dehydrated body will age. However, I have seen the future I hoped to see, and for this I am happy.{	
\u8220?Please accept our respects,\u8221? Luo Ji said.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}I only wish to discuss with you one possibility: Perhaps seeds of love are present in other places in the universe. We ought to encourage them to sprout and grow.{	
\u8220?That\u8217?s a goal worth taking risks for.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}Yes, we can take risks.{	
\u8220?I have a dream that one day brilliant sunlight will illuminate the dark forest.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
The sun was setting. Now only its tip was exposed beyond the distant mountains, as if the mountaintop was inset with a dazzling gemstone. Like the grass, the child running in the distance was bathed in the golden sunset.\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}The sun will set soon. Isn\u8217?t your child afraid?{	
\u8220?Of course she\u8217?s not afraid. She knows that the sun will rise again tomorrow.\u8221?\par\pard\plain\hyphpar}{	
